Joe Biden has been sworn in as the 46th President of the United States . He took his oath of office Wednesday at the US Capitol, ending the Donald Trump era. Biden, surrounded by his family, took the oath of office at 11:49 a.m. at a ceremony at the well protected US Capitol. The oath of office was administered by US Chief Justice John Roberts, at the ceremony attended by former President Bill Clinton and wife Hillary, former President George Bush and Wife Laura, former President Barack Obama and wife Michelle, and Vice President Mike Pence and his wife Karen.